    "_id": "5b60756260a036b8",
    "name": "Arboreal Arms",
    "type": "spell",
    "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/spell.webp",
    "effects": [],
    "folder": null,
    "sort": 0,
    "flags": {},
    "system": {
      "description": {
        "value": "<p>You crumble a small piece of bark in your hand and transform one or both of your arms into massive branches or trunks. One or both of your hands takes the shape of a thick trunk that can be used to make unarmed attacks. This attack deals 1d8 bludgeoning damage, has the grapple and sweep traits, and is in the club group. Small roots extend from the end of the trunk and allow you to Interact with objects, but you cannot wield a weapon in this hand. Instead of the normal critical specialization effect, if you roll a critical success on an attack with <em>arboreal arms</em> the small roots at the end of the trunk extend out and wrap around some part of your foe's body; you may make a Grapple attempt as a free action. This Grapple attempt doesn't count toward your multiple attack penalty, and your multiple attack penalty doesn't apply to this Grapple check. This unarmed attack is a valid target for <em>shillelagh</em>.\n<p>The duration increases to 10 minutes and you can Dismiss the spell to end its duration early.\n</p>"
      },
      "source": {
        "value": "Everything Archetypes: Wilderness"
      },
