    "folder": null,
    "sort": 0,
    "flags": {},
    "system": {
      "description": {
        "value": "<p>You crumble a small piece of bark onto your legs and they become covered in bark and take on the power of supple trees. For the duration you are immune to forced movement, unless you are willing to be moved.\n</p>\n<p>\nWhen you take the Leap action you may jump up to your Speed or 30 feet, whichever is higher, in any direction. You must land on a space of solid ground or else you fall after using your next action.\n</p>\n<p>\nIf your next action after Leaping is a Strike you impart the energy of your leap into your attack; the Strike gains a circumstance bonus to damage equal to 2 per damage die of your weapon or unarmed attack.\n</p>\n<p>\nYou can exert a great deal of control over this transformation. You may choose to create truly massive arboreal legs, increasing your size to Large. If you do so, this spell gains the polymorph trait, and your reach increases by 5 feet (or by 10 feet if you started out tiny). If you are also activating <em>arboreal arms</em> or <em>arboreal bole</em> when casting this spell, you may choose\n</p>"
      },
