  {
    "_id": "a30f059e7d0fd09e",
    "name": "Forest Avenger",
    "type": "spell",
    "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/spell.webp",
    "effects": [],
    "folder": null,
    "sort": 0,
    "flags": {},
    "system": {
      "description": {
        "value": "<p>You take the form of a powerful arboreal, a living, walking tree, assuming a Huge battle form. Your arms become branches and your fingers become twigs with leaves. Your legs are like the trunks of a tree. While in this form you gain the plant trait. You can speak while in this form. You can Dismiss this spell.\n</p>\n<p>\nYou gain the following statistics and abilities:\n</p>\n<p>\n<ul>\n<li>AC = 21 + your level. Ignore your armor's check penalty and Speed reduction.</li>\n<li>15 temporary Hit Points.</li>\n<li>Speed 40 feet.</li>\n<li>Resistance 10 to physical.</li>\n<li>Darkvision and tremorsense 60 feet.</li>\n<li>Athletics modifier of +30, unless your own modifier is higher.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<p>\nYou gain the following melee attacks, which are the only attacks you can use. You are trained with them. Your attack modifier is +28, and you use the listed damage. These attacks are Strength based (for the purpose of the enfeebled condition, for example). If your unarmed attack modifier is higher, you can use it instead.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n<strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> branch (reach 20 feet), <strong>Damage</strong> 3d12 + 15 bludgeoning\n</p>\n<p>\n<strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> trunk (agile, reach 15 feet), <strong>Damage</strong> 3d8 + 15 bludgeoning\n</p>"
      },
      "source": {
        "value": "Everything Archetypes: Wilderness"
      },
